        <!-- ======= About Section ======= -->
        <section id="about" class="about">
            <div class="container">

                <div class="section-title">

                    <h3>Learn More <span>About KOLAROO</span></h3>
            
                </div>

                <div class="row content">
                    <div class="col-lg-6">
                        <p>

                        </p>
                        <ul style="line-height: 2.5; font-family: cursive;color: rgb(8, 117, 150); font-size: 18px;">
                            <li><i class="ri-check-double-line"></i> There are only 1897 threaten species left in Australia!</li>
                            <li><i class="ri-check-double-line"></i> There are only 282 threaten species left in Victoria!</li>
                            <li><i class="ri-check-double-line"></i> There are only 63 threaten species left in Melbourne!</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-6 pt-4 pt-lg-0">

                        <p style="line-height: 2.5;">
                            75 species go extinct every day around the world, and 3 species are labelled dead every hour. Many species have disappeared from the earth before scientists can describe and name them, and the rate of extinction is increasing by a hundredfold.
                        </p>
                        <a href="#services" class="btn-learn-more">Learn More</a>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </section><!-- End About Section -->


        <section id="services" class="services">
            <div class="section-title">
                <div class="container" data-aos="fade-up" style="background-color: aliceblue;">
                    <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
                                <a href="@Url.Action("landanimals","Home")">
                                    <img src="~/assets/img/Homelandanimal.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="" style="width: 1000px; height: 400px;">
                                </a>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100" style="line-height:2.5; font-size: 18px;">
                                <br><br><br>
                                <p>

                                    Australia is known for its biodiversity and the mainland is rich in some of the world's most iconic animals. But a wide range of threatened species have been destroyed in multiple human activity tragedies. Let's learn more about them


                                </p>
                            </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">

                        <div class="col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100"
                             style="line-height:2; font-family: Arial; font-size: 18px;">
                            <br><br><br>
                            <p>
                                In Australia today, millions of hectares of habitat are not permanently protected. Sadly, without a lasting form of protection, habitats can be degraded or destroyed and species extinction rates are high. Habitat is protected not only because it protects native plants, birds and animals, but also because it protects us.

                            </p>
                        </div>
                            <div class="col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
